# Email capture for "the signal list" (the Transmissions section).
# Set this to a form-POST URL from a free service — Formspree, Getform, or
# Buttondown all give you one with no code:
#   - Formspree:  https://formspree.io/f/XXXXXXXX
#   - Getform:    https://getform.io/f/XXXXXXXX
# Then redeploy. Until it's set, the section shows a "Follow on Bandcamp"
# fallback instead of a form that goes nowhere.
VITE_SUBSCRIBE_ENDPOINT=

# ── Launch film (optional) ────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Host the reactive launch film on a CDN (Cloudflare R2, Vercel Blob, …) instead
# of committing a large file to src/assets/video/. Set the absolute URL(s) below
# and redeploy — they take precedence over any local launch.mp4.
#
# IMPORTANT: the launch film drives the audio-reactive visualizer, so its host
# MUST send an `Access-Control-Allow-Origin` header (the site loads it with
# crossOrigin="anonymous"). Without CORS the film still plays, but the site
# won't pulse to it. Gallery films in src/data/videos.ts have no such rule.
VITE_LAUNCH_VIDEO_URL=
# Optional lighter encode served to phones (falls back to the desktop URL):
VITE_LAUNCH_VIDEO_MOBILE_URL=
# Optional poster frame shown before the film loads:
VITE_LAUNCH_POSTER_URL=
